Here's a breakdown of how to create a web form using HTML and process it with PHP to save user input to a database:

**1. HTML Form (index.html):**

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>User Input Form</title>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Enter Your Name</h1>
  <form method="post" action="process.php">
    <label for="name">Name:</label>
    <input type="text" id="name" name="name" required>
    <br><br>
    <input type="submit" value="Submit">
  </form>
</body>
</html>
```

* **`<form>` tag:**
    * `method="post"`: Specifies that data will be sent using the HTTP POST method (more secure for sensitive data).
    * `action="process.php"`: Indicates that the form data will be sent to the `process.php` file for processing.
* **`<label>` tag:** Provides a descriptive label for the input field.
* **`<input>` tag:**
    * `type="text"`: Creates a text input field.
    * `id="name"`: Gives the field a unique identifier.
    * `name="name"`: Assigns a name to the field, which will be used to access the data in PHP.
    * `required`: Makes the field mandatory.
* **`<input type="submit">`:** Creates the submit button.

**2. PHP Processing Script (process.php):**

```php
<?php

// Database connection details
$servername = "localhost";
$username = "your_username";
$password = "your_password";
$dbname = "your_database";

// Create connection
$conn = new mysqli($servername, $username, $password, $dbname);

// Check connection
if ($conn->connect_error) {
  die("Connection failed: " . $conn->connect_error);
}

// Get user input from the form
$name = $_POST["name"];

// Prepare and execute the SQL query
$sql = "INSERT INTO users (name) VALUES ('$name')";

if ($conn->query($sql) === TRUE) {
  echo "New record created successfully";
} else {
  echo "Error: " . $sql . "<br>" . $conn->error;
}

// Close the database connection
$conn->close();

?>
```

* **Database Connection:**
    * Replace `your_username`, `your_password`, and `your_database` with your actual database credentials.
    * The code establishes a connection to the MySQL database.
* **Input Retrieval:**
    * `$_POST["name"]`: Accesses the value submitted in the `name` field of the form.
* **SQL Query:**
    * `INSERT INTO users (name) VALUES ('$name')`: Inserts the user's name into a table named `users`.
* **Error Handling:**
    * Checks for errors during the database query and displays an error message if necessary.
* **Database Closure:**
    * Closes the database connection to release resources.

**3. Running the Code:**

* Save both `index.html` and `process.php` files in the same directory.
* Make sure you have a MySQL database set up and running.
* Access `index.html` in your web browser.
* Enter your name in the form and click "Submit."
* The data will be sent to `process.php`, which will save it to the database.



